sub_title: Associate Professor at UMC Utrecht dept of Cardiology
summary:
René was trained as a technical physician at the University of Twente. He completed his master track
MEDICAL IMAGING & INTERVENTIONS in 2012. 

Medical Imaging and Interventions deals with minimal invasive technology, reconstruction of damaged tissues, medical robotics, computer controlled interventions, biomaterials and advanced imaging and localization techniques.

http://www.utwente.nl/tg/education/mastertracks/mii/ 

In 2016, René successfully  defended his PhD thesis entitled "Technological Advances in Catheter Based Cardiac Therapies . René is currently working as a Postdoc  at the University Medical Center in Utrecht, department of Cardiology.
